This paper focuses on the joint coverage analysis of a cellular-based IoT network powered by ambient RF energy harvesting. The paper discusses the time division-based approach for power and information transmission, which is a common topic in the network and information theory literature (cs.IT). The paper also considers the system-level performance of the IoT network, which involves the interaction between multiple devices and the cellular network (cs.SY). The use of RF energy harvesting and IoT devices suggests a focus on wireless communication and networking (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses throughput optimization and system design insights, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and optimization literature (cs.MM, cs.MA).
